</head>
<body>


    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🍩 Medu Vada</h1>
        

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Urad Dal (Black Gram Lentils)</li>
            <li>2 Green Chilies (Finely Chopped)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Black Pepper (Crushed)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Coriander Leaves (Chopped)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Curry Leaves (Chopped)</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Hing (Asafoetida)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <h3>Step 1: Soak and Grind</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Wash and soak urad dal for 4-5 hours.</li>
            <li>Drain the water and grind into a smooth batter without adding too much water.</li>
            <li>Transfer to a bowl and whisk the batter to make it fluffy.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 2: Mix Ingredients</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Add chopped green chilies, black pepper, cumin seeds, coriander, curry leaves, hing, and salt.</li>
            <li>Mix well.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 3: Shape and Fry</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Heat oil in a deep pan.</li>
            <li>Wet your hands, take a small portion of batter, make a hole in the center, and gently slide into the hot oil.</li>
            <li>Fry until golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>Drain excess oil on a paper towel.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 4: Serve</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
